ConnectforHealth 

Your invite to Cigna Healthcare's wellbeing webinar series 

At Cigna Healthcare, we recognize the importance of prioritizing your health and wellbeing. As your health and wellness partner, we are fully committed to helping you establish healthy habits. 

You are invited to join Cigna Healthcare’s Connect for Health webinar on: 

Understanding Monkeypox: Symptoms, Transmission and Prevention 

Join us tomorrow as our experts break down the monkeypox outbreak, offering guidance on risk factors, safety measures and public health recommendations. Seek clarity and learn how to adapt your prevention efforts effectively. 

 	  	  <https://image2.comms.cigna.com/EloquaImages/clients/CignaGHBIntl/%7Bc126220d-91e1-40d2-b6cb-df0b6286d51c%7D_2023-brand-leaf.png> 	 	 Save the date

Infectious Diseases Specialist, The Nairobi Hospital 

Dr Eric Munene is a consultant physician trained in infectious diseases at the University of Nairobi (UON), London School of Hygiene and Tropical Medicine, and University of Washington. He is an honorary lecturer at the University of Nairobi in the department of tropical/ infectious diseases, travel medicine, epidemiology, and biostatistics. He is also the Chairman of Infectious Diseases Committee at the Nairobi Hospital.
